England defeated Belgium 1-0 in its
final exhibition match before the European soccer championship.  Danny Welbeck  scored in the 36th minute at Wembley Stadium
in London to give manager  Roy Hodgson  a win in his first home
match. Hodgson, who replaced Fabio Capello last month, won his
England debut 1-0 in Norway on May 27.  England opens play at Euro 2012 against France on June 11.
The 16-team tournament co-hosted by Poland and Ukraine begins 
June 8 with the final to be played July 1.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
